<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1327,283,1070]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,763,789]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species appears to be much like 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1014,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[904,1014,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">G. stenos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1030,1122,764,790]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The two may be separated not only by the differences in the male and female genitalia but also by the much lighter yellow color of the tomentum in 
<emphasis box="[734,874,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName box="[734,869,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cressoni" status="sp. nov.">G. cressoni</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[881,972,844,870]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
